#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:1
msgid "Saving & Executing DRDs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:3
msgid ""
"When a chain is DRD-compatible (green validation), you can save it as a "
"Decision Requirements Diagram template. This deploys a unified DRD to "
"Operaton and stores the template locally for reuse."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:7
msgid "Saving a DRD"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:9
msgid ""
"Build a chain that shows green validation status (\"Chain is valid and ready "
"to execute\")."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:10
msgid "Click **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:11
msgid ""
"The Save modal opens showing a purple 🎯 DRD badge, confirming the chain "
"qualifies for DRD deployment."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:12
msgid "Enter a name and optional description."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:13
msgid "Click **Save as DRD**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:15
msgid ""
"The system assembles the DMN XML with proper `<informationRequirement>` "
"wiring, deploys it to Operaton, and stores the template in your browser's "
"local storage. A success message shows the Operaton deployment ID."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:19
msgid "Saving a sequential template"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:21
msgid ""
"If the chain has amber validation (sequential execution required), clicking "
"**Save** opens the same modal but shows a sequential template badge instead "
"of a DRD badge. The template is saved locally for reuse but is not deployed "
"to Operaton as a unified DRD."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:25
msgid "My Templates"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:27
msgid ""
"Saved templates appear in the **My Templates** section of the Configuration "
"panel."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:34
msgid ""
"Each template card shows its name, description, type badge (🔗 DRD or "
"sequential), and the endpoint it was saved for. Click a template card to "
"load it into the Chain Composer. Templates are endpoint-scoped — templates "
"saved for one TriplyDB dataset do not appear when a different endpoint is "
"active."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:38
msgid "Executing a DRD template"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:40
msgid ""
"Loading a DRD template and clicking **Execute** sends a single API call to "
"Operaton, referencing the DRD entry-point identifier. Operaton evaluates the "
"full chain internally and returns the final result in one response. This is "
"typically 50% faster than sequential execution for a two-step chain."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:44
msgid "Using a DRD in a BPMN process"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:46
msgid ""
"DRD templates appear in the BPMN Modeler's **Link to DMN/DRD** dropdown "
"under the \"🔗 DRDs (Unified Chains)\" group. Selecting one auto-populates "
"the `camunda:decisionRef` attribute with the DRD entry-point identifier, so "
"a single `BusinessRuleTask` in your BPMN process can invoke the entire chain."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:50
msgid "Notes on local storage"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdrd-generation.md:52
msgid ""
"DRD templates are stored in `localStorage` and are scoped to the browser and "
"device. They are not shared between users or between browsers. If you clear "
"browser storage, templates are lost. Export the chain as JSON before "
"clearing storage if you want to preserve it. A server-side template registry "
"is planned for Phase 2."
msgstr ""
